    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Ornate frames, usually gilded, distinguished by curvilinear shapes resembling ears or earlobes; based on a style developed by silversmiths in the Netherlands ca. 1600; may include shapes of masks and marine life.</Note_Text>
